    </div>
    <div class="flex-content-right pl-100">
      <p>By 1945, Roberto Larin expanded the family's coffee production with wet and dry mills and named the mill “El ‘98”, which traces back to the original founding date of 1798. Passed down through six generations, devotion to coffee and this beloved land becomes a legacy of the Larin family. Today, that dedication remains strong as each era passes the torch of excellence. Andres and Jose Larin carry on their ancestors’ innovations and contributions, by infusing a family tradition with creative innovations.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="flex-image-first">
